I have been shopping for jewelry and I would appreciate any assistance in determining what would be a fair price for some items.  I don't want to be a conned rogue, that would be embarassing :-)<br>
<br>
Specifically, I'm interested in the following items:<br>
Enchanted electrum ring with star ruby (+7 cha, +5 dex)<br>
Enchanted platinum ring with star ruby (+5 cha, +7 dex)<br>
<br>
Thank you for any information :-)<br>
Soyin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umorgenayanamii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morgen Ayanamii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lorekeeper</span><br>  Posts: 216<br> <font color=#660000>(2/14/02 11:59:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=274.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I need guidance buying jewelry</span><hr size=1> Star rubies cost around 70 pp.  <br>
electrum bars between 2.5 and 3 pp. <br>
gold bars cost around 11 pp each.<br>
platinum bars around 105-110 pp. <br>
<br>
If you buy the materials, and an enchanter is successful at the attempt, it could cost you as little as the sum of the parts.   If they fail, you have to try again.  You just doubled your cost. <br>
<br>
Most enchanters work it over the long run and have retail prices they charge for everything. <br>
<br>
I tend to work for cost and group people so they can tell if I succeed or fail.  I can save them money by buying the materials cheaper than they could.  This is great for when I'm successful.  Not so great if they scrimp and save and I fail.<br>
<br>
But paying 360 pp for a platinum star ruby veil is not unreasonable.  Other jewelers will have prices that vary from this up or down, if you buy it made.  the electrum star ruby rings you can figure out as well. <br>
<br>
Talk to your jeweler first.  If you don't understand something, ask.  <br>
<br>
btw, it's electrum and gold star ruby rings, platinum veil.<br>
<br>
Morgen <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umorgenayanamii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morgen Ayanamii</A> at: 2/15/02 12:00:32 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/usoyinmilka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soyin Milka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#660000>(2/15/02 1:22:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=274.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I need guidance buying jewelry</span><hr size=1> Hello,<br>
First, thank you for taking the time to answer Morgen.<br>
I really want rings and not a veil, so I guess I got confused with some of the parts.  I would prefer the rings giving +5 in charisma and +7 in dexterity.  If I understood you correctly, this would be the enchanted gold with star ruby rings.<br>
<br>
It would also cost 81 PPs per attempt to make them... Ow.<br>
It would explain the prices I have been asked for by jewellers.  I know you are already pretty busy and in demand Morgen, but I would appreciate if you could do them for me.  I don't know the complexity level of these rings, but I would not cringe if it took three attempts to make two rings.  It would still cost me significantly less than from the two jewellers I talked to so far.  It doesn't have to be anytime soon either.  <br>
<br>
In any case, thank you for your help :-)<br>
Soyin.<br>
