<br>
About 2400 pp or so from now I should be up high enough to do gold star rubies, I *hope*.   To finish out electrum should take me somewhere from 800 to 1200 pp, I'm guessing.<br>
<br>
Jewelry making is fun.  But one of the reasons I've been trying to level is so I can make the money more easily so that I can go up in jewelcraft.  I can finally hunt Hill Giants (not solo, in a group), so i can get 1/6th of whatever take that is.  They're only yellow to me now, mostly.  I can get better equipment than I can get the cash to afford.  And I don't really sell stuff.  I tend to give it away to folks.  And I consistently hunt with NBG people, so it's very rare that an evening turns up extra sellable magic anyway.<br>
<br>
I'm not willing to spend my sister's money doing jewelry I haven't trivialed yet.  The failure rate is too high, the investment is too high.  Even *when* trivialed, I feel bad when something fails (ask Wiestrum about that).<br>
<br>
Ledenyetz troupe has a very nice jeweler.  If he is up to gold star rubies, I suggest you talk to him, and mention that I referred you.  He has specific prices and he does't haggle, but they are decent prices.<br>
<br>
Good luck.  <br>
<br>
Morgen<br>
